l responsibility for end-of-life management, incentivizing producers to use recyclable materials and funding collection/sorting infrastructure. Italy\'s Ronchi Decree raised separate collection from 9% in 1997 to 66.6% in 2023.\n- **Confidence**: literature_backed\n\n## Data Source\n- **Name**: Product Stewardship Institute EPR legislation tracker\n- **Organization**: Product Stewardship Institute\n- **URL**: https://epr.sustainablepackaging.org\n- **Format**: Interactive legislation database\n- **Accessibility**: open\n- **Coverage**: OECD countries, 7 US states as of 2025\n\n## References from Literature\nThe following references were cited in the research report. You can use `requests.get()`\nto fetch URLs below and verify the reported statistic and assess citation quality.\n- https://epr.sustainablepackaging.org\n- https://ecostar.eu.com/municipal-solid-waste-treatment-around-the-world-ecostar/\n\n## EPI Target Data Summary\n**Target Indicator**: WRR — Rate of recovery of energy of materials from waste (proportion composted, recycled, or incinerated with energy recovery_\n**Units**: proportion\n**Polarity**: positive\n**Source**: Various\n**Data File**: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/docs/EPI2024_Work/Raw/WRR_raw.csv`\n**Coverage**: 140 countries, 2016-2022 (450 observations)\n**Summary Stats**: mean=0.40, std=0.36, median=0.24\n\n**Control Variable Files**:\n- GPC: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/docs/EPI2024_Work/Raw/GPC_raw.csv`\n- POP: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/docs/EPI2024_Work/Raw/POP_raw.csv`\n- URB: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/docs/EPI2024_Work/Raw/URB_raw.csv`\n\n## Caveats to Consider\n- Implementation delays of 1-3 years common\n- Enforcement variability across countries\n- Design heterogeneity in program structure\n- Confounding with other waste legislation\n- Reverse causality concern\n\n## Output Directory\nWrite ALL output files to: `/Users/samkouteili/rose/epi/multi-agent/outputs/WRR/stage2/WRR-H04/`